# Raw Cypher / Graph Query Equivalents

Attempted: cleo nexus --help | grep -i 'query|cypher|raw|sql|gql'
Result: NO raw query or cypher surface found.

Available code-intelligence query surface:
- cleo nexus context <symbol>   — callers/callees/community/processes for a named symbol
- cleo nexus impact <symbol>    — blast radius at depth 1/2/3
- cleo nexus clusters           — list all Louvain communities
- cleo nexus flows              — list all traced execution processes
- cleo nexus export --format gexf   — export full graph as GEXF XML for Gephi
- cleo nexus export --format json   — export full graph as JSON

GAP: No raw graph traversal language (Cypher, GQL, SPARQL, GraphQL) is exposed.
GAP: No way to query: 'find all symbols in community X that import module Y'
GAP: No way to query: 'show me all paths between A and B'
GAP: context/impact queries require an exact symbol name — no fuzzy/semantic code search
